The paper deals with reinforcement learning (RL) using high-dimensional observations, specifically learning a closed-loop control policy from pixel information only. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). Among these, machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a data-efficient RL algorithm using deep dynamical models. Computer vision is also a likely category, as the paper deals with learning from image pixels. Robotics and control systems are less likely but still possible categories, as the paper deals with closed-loop control policies.
